“Short-term pain for long-term gain.”The one thing I thought I had going for me was that blue checkmark on Twitter.
pic.twitter.com/z0zvYVTpxD — Kelsey Bolar (Harkness) (@kelseybolar) February 25, 2019Until shortly after making the announcement—there was no longer a blue checkmark next to my Twitter handle.
Given Twitter’s reputation among conservatives, I was confident I’d gin up enough outrage to publicly shame them into giving me the blue checkmark back.
I put my accusations on hold and decided to reach out to a contact at Twitter to explain the situation.
Out of the blue, less than two weeks later, my blue checkmark was back.